
---


@startuml

' Define classes
class WebPortal {
    +versionNumber: String
    +url: String
    +buildings: Set<Building>
}

class Building {
    +id: String
    +name: String
    +energyClass: String (A, B, C, D)
    +address: String
    +yearOfConstruction: Integer
    +owner: User
    +additionalEntries: Set<AdditionalEntry>
    +images: Set<Image>
    +profilePhoto: Image
}

class AdditionalEntry {
    +name: String
    +value: Object
    +unit: String
    +isPublic: Boolean
    +building: Building
}

class Image {
    +fileName: String
    +building: Building
}

class User {
    +username: String
    +email: String
    +password: String
    +isAdmin: Boolean
    +buildings: Set<Building>
    +comments: Set<Comment>
}

class Comment {
    +text: String
    +user: User
    +building: Building
}

class Administrator {
    -- User
    +idCardNumber: String
}

' Relationships
WebPortal "1" -- "0..*" Building : has
Building "1" -- "1" User : owned by
User "1" -- "0..*" AdditionalEntry : creates
AdditionalEntry "1" -- "1" Building : belongs to
Building "1" -- "0..*" Image : has
Image "1" -- "1" Building : belongs to
User "1" -- "0..*" Comment : comments on
Comment "1" -- "1" User : made by
Comment "1" -- "1" Building : refers to
Administrator "1" -- "1" User : is a type of

' Use Cases
actor Visitor
actor User
actor Administrator

usecase "Register as User" as UC1
usecase "Confirm Email" as UC2
usecase "Activate Account" as UC3
usecase "Search Buildings" as UC4
usecase "Create Building" as UC5
usecase "Manage Entries" as UC6
usecase "Comment on Building" as UC7
usecase "View Public Entries" as UC8
usecase "Delete Comment" as UC9
usecase "Set Up User" as UC10

Visitor --> UC1
Visitor --> UC4
User --> UC1
User --> UC5
User --> UC6
User --> UC7
User --> UC8
Administrator --> UC10
Administrator --> UC9

@enduml

---

## ✅ Use Cases and Actors

| Use Case | Actor(s)         | Description |
|----------|------------------|-------------|
| UC1      | Visitor, User    | Register as a user with username, email, and password. |
| UC2      | Visitor          | Confirm email via a link sent after registration. |
| UC3      | System           | Automatically activate user account after confirmation and admin setup. |
| UC4      | Visitor          | Search for buildings using full-text search. |
| UC5      | User             | Create a new building in the portal. |
| UC6      | User             | Manage additional entries (add, edit, delete). |
| UC7      | User             | Comment on other users’ buildings. |
| UC8      | Visitor          | View public additional entries of a building. |
| UC9      | Administrator    | Delete comments from any user. |
| UC10     | Administrator    | Set up or manage user accounts (create, edit, delete). |

---

## 🧠 Notes

- **Generalization**: `Administrator` is a special type of `User`.
- **Relationships**:
  - A `WebPortal` contains multiple `Buildings`.
  - Each `Building` is owned by one `User`.
  - A `User` can create multiple `Buildings`, `Comments`, and `AdditionalEntries`.
  - `AdditionalEntries` can be either textual or numeric with a unit.
  - `Images` are associated with `Buildings`, and one image is selected as the profile photo.
- **Use Cases** are grouped logically by actors and include both public and private functions.

